main event: On August 23, 1957, there was a UFO sighting in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania involving two very bright objects observed by ground-radar for a few seconds.
interesting points: The observation involved two very bright objects that were close together.
The length of the observation was only a few seconds.
The report mentioned that there were no photographs taken of the objects.
A probable sighting of SAC aircraft in the area was also reported, indicating possible military presence in the vicinity of the UFO sighting.
The senior controller of the 25th Air Division suggested that the objects might have been SAC aircraft on a mission to the southwest of Philadelphia.
witnesses: unspecified ground-radar observer and 1/Lt. Owen P. Lynch, senior controller of the 25th Air Division
